{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> αἱρετ-ός</b>, ή, όν, <br /> <br /><Level1><b>__A</b></Level1> <b>that may be taken</b> or <b>conquered</b>, δόλῳ[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 4.201\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>to be understood</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedo” 81b. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__A.II</b></Level2> (αἱρέομαι) <b>to be chosen, eligible</b>, opposed to φευκτός, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Philebus” 21df, 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Ethica Nicomachea” 1097a32, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: frequently in <i>comparative</i> or <i>superlative</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.126, 156, +others; ζόης πονηρᾶς θάνατος αἱρετώτερος 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Fragmenta - American Journal of Philology” 401. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__A.II.2</b></Level3> <b>chosen, elected</b>, especially opposed to κληρωτός, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 12.154, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 759b, 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Politica” 1294b9, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 915c, 4th c.BC: Aeschines Orator 3.13; αἱ. βασιλῆς 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Menexenus” 238d; τυραννίς 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Politica” 1285a31:\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] —αἱ. ἄνδρες <b>commissioners</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Lycurgus” 26. οἱ αἱ. 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 1.3.21\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: = Latin <i>optiones</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 6th c.AD: Lydus, Joannes Laurentius Historicus “Mag.” 1.46. \">Refs 6th c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__A.II.3</b></Level3> <b>that may be chosen</b>, opposed to αἱρετέος (which see), [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Chrysippus Stoicus 3.22.\">